House Bill 722
By: Representatives Stephens of the 164th, Petrea of the 166th, and Franklin of the 160th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend an Act establishing the State Court of Bryan County (formerly the City Court of
2 Pembroke), approved January 10, 1938 (Ga. L. 1937-38, Ex. Sess., p. 714), as amended,
3 particularly by an Act approved May 1, 2023 (Ga. L. 2023, p. 3851), so as to establish the
4 position of chief judge; to provide for a new part-time associate judge; to provide for the
5 initial appointment of such associate judge by the Governor; to provide for the elections and
6 terms of office of the judges of the court; to provide for compensation of the judges; to
7 provide for an effective date; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and
8 for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 An Act establishing the State Court of Bryan County (formerly the City Court of Pembroke),
12 approved January 10, 1938 (Ga. L. 1937-38, Ex. Sess., p. 714), as amended, particularly by
13 an Act approved May 1, 2023 (Ga. L. 2023, p. 3851), is amended by revising Section 1.1 as
14 follows:
H. B. 722
- 1 -

