15 "SECTION 1.1.
16 There shall be one full-time chief judge of the State Court of Bryan County, who shall be
17 the present judge of said Court at the time of the effective date of this Act, and one
18 associate judge of such court. The chief judge shall serve the remainder of the term of
19 office to which he or she was elected. Future successors of the chief judge shall be elected
20 at the general election conducted immediately prior to the expiration of the term of office,
21 and they shall take office on the first day of January following their election and serve for
22 a term of office of four years and until their successors are duly elected and qualified. Said
23 chief judge shall have and may exercise all powers, duties, jurisdictions, privileges, and
24 immunities of the present judge of the State Court of Bryan County and shall serve in a
25 full-time capacity as permitted by O.C.G.A. Section 15-7-20. The compensation of the
26 chief judge shall be set by local act of the governing authority of Bryan County. The chief
27 judge of the state court shall receive all legally required benefits. The governing authority
28 of Bryan County may supplement such judge's salary. All of the expenditures authorized
29 herein are declared to be an expense of court and payable out of the county treasury as
30 such."
31 SECTION 2.
32 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 1.2 as follows:
33 "SECTION 1.2.
34 The new position of associate judge of the state court shall be a part-time position, and such
35 judge shall not be permitted to engage in the practice of law in the State Court of Bryan
36 County. The associate judge as provided by this Act shall be appointed by the Governor
37 for a term beginning January 1, 2026, and expiring December 31, 2028, and until a
38 successor is elected and qualified. A successor to the associate judge shall be elected in
39 the manner provided by Code Section 21-2-138 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated
