40 for the election of judges of the state courts in 2028 for a term of four years beginning on
41 January 1, 2029, and until the election and qualification of a successor. The associate
42 judge shall take office on the first day of January following the date of election. Said
43 associate judge shall have and may exercise all powers, duties, jurisdictions, privileges, and
44 immunities of the present judge of the State Court of Bryan County. The compensation of
45 the associate judge shall be set by local act of the governing authority of Bryan County.
46 The associate judge of the state court shall receive all legally required benefits. The
47 governing authority of Bryan County may supplement such judge's salary. All of the
48 expenditures authorized herein are declared to be an expense of court and payable out of
49 the county treasury as such."
50 SECTION 3.
51 Said Act is further amended by adding a new section to read as follows:
52 "SECTION 1.3.
53 Each judge of the State Court of Bryan County shall have such qualifications and shall be
54 subject to such restrictions and discipline as provided in Chapter 7 of Title 15 of the
55 Official Code of Georgia Annotated."
56 SECTION 4.
57 Said Act is further amended by adding a new section to read as follows:
58 "SECTION 1.4.
59 The full-time judge of the State Court of Bryan County shall be the chief judge of said
60 court. The chief judge shall have responsibility for the administration of the operations of
61 the State Court of Bryan County, including, but not limited to, budgeting, scheduling, and
62 the policies, rules, and standing orders of the State Court of Bryan County."
